hropshire, England":"Stretton, Staffordshire, England","Stretton by Burton upon Trent, Staffordshire, England":"Stretton by Burton upon Trent, Staffordshire, England, United Kingdom","Alderley, Cheshire, England":"Alderley, Cheshire, England","Birdstone, Herefordshire, England":"Herefordshire, England, United Kingdom"},"nl":{"1436–1515":"1436–1515","1432–1482":"1432–1482","1458–1504":"1458–1504","1483–1583":"1483–1583","1418–1456":"1418–1456","1420–1473":"1420–1473","25 September 1473":"25 september 1473","1473":"1473","1583":"1583","1483":"1483","1482":"1482","1436":"1436","1458":"1458","1457":"1457","1456":"1456","1455":"1455","1432":"1432","1420":"1420","1418":"1418","1504":"1504","1515":"1515","Stretton, Staffordshire, England":"Stretton, Staffordshire, England","Glazeley, Shropshire, England":"Glazeley, Shropshire, England","Stretton, Shropshire, England":"Stretton, Staffordshire, England","Stretton by Burton upon Trent, Staffordshire, England":"Stretton by Burton upon Trent, Staffordshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Alderley, Cheshire, England":"Alderley, Cheshire, England","Birdstone, Herefordshire, England":"Herefordshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"1436–1515":"1436–1515","1432–1482":"1432–1482","1458–1504":"1458–1504","1483–1583":"1483–1583","1418–1456":"1418–1456","1420–1473":"1420–1473","25 September 1473":"25 September 1473","1473":"1473","1583":"1583","1483":"1483","1482":"1482","1436":"1436","1458":"1458","1457":"1457","1456":"1456","1455":"1455","1432":"1432","1420":"1420","1418":"1418","1504":"1504","1515":"1515","Stretton, Staffordshire, England":"Stretton, Staffordshire, England","Glazeley, Shropshire, England":"Glazeley, Shropshire, England","Stretton, Shropshire, England":"Stretton, Staffordshire, England","Stretton by Burton upon Trent, Staffordshire, England":"Stretton by Burton upon Trent, Staffordshire, England, United Kingdom","Alderley, Cheshire, England":"Alderley, Cheshire, England","Birdstone, Herefordshire, England":"Herefordshire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Wilde","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Irish, English, and German: variant of   Wild  . This is the usual form of the surname in Ireland.","Dutch: variant of   De Wilde  .","History: The writer Oscar Wilde (1854–1900) was born in Dublin, Ireland, descended from Ralph Wilde, a builder from Walsingham near Durham, England, who had moved to Ireland in the 17th century. Richard Henry Wilde (1789–1847), born in Dublin, emigrated to Baltimore, MD, in 1797 and was raised in GA, where he became a congressman (1815–17, 1827–35). He moved to New Orleans, LA, in 1843 and was a professor at the University of LA (now Tulane)."],"variants":[{"name":"Wild","meanings":["English: from Middle English <i>wilde</i> ‘wild, violent’ (Old English <i>wilde</i>), hence a nickname for a man of violent and undisciplined character, or a topographic name for someone who lived on a patch of overgrown uncultivated land (from Middle English <i>wilde</i> (noun) ‘wild place, wasteland’).","English: variant of   Wile  , with excrescent <i>-d</i>.","German and Jewish (Ashkenazic): cognate of 1 above, from Middle High German <i>wilde</i>, <i>wilt</i>, German <i>wild</i> ‘wild’, also used in the sense ‘strange, foreign’, and therefore in some cases a nickname for an incomer."]}]},{"name":"Sarah","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Biblical name, borne by the wife of Abraham and mother of Isaac. According to the Book of Genesis, she was originally called <i>Sarai</i> (possibly meaning ‘contentious’ in Hebrew), but had her name changed by God to the more auspicious <i>Sarah</i> ‘princess’ in token of a greater blessing (Genesis 17:15, ‘And God said unto Abraham, As for Sarai thy wife, thou shalt not call her name Sarai, but Sarah shall her name be’). This has been one of the most enduringly popular girls' names."],"variants":[{"name":"Sara","meanings":["Variant of   Sarah .  This is the form used in the Greek of the New Testament (Hebrews 11:11)."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705197,"age":19,"year":"1455","julianDay":2252488,"title":"Wars of the Roses","description":"Wars of the Roses was a series of English civil wars for control of the throne of England between the royal families House of Lancaster and the House of York. The name of the war was derived as the red rose was the symbol of the Lancastrians and the white rose was the symbol of the Yorks.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/british-history/wars-of-the-roses","urlTitle":"History - Wars of the Roses","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Sarah Wilde was born in 1436, in Stretton, Staffordshire, England, her father, Sir T W B Wylde Of Bromham, was 18 and her mother, Lady E Ragon Baroness Wylde, was 17. She married Sir Richard Wainwright Higgins in 1457, in Stretton by Burton upon Trent, Staffordshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 1 daughter. She died in 1515, in her hometown, at the age of 79."},"et":{"1436–1515":"1436–1515","1432–1482":"1432–1482","1458–1504":"1458–1504","1483–1583":"1483–1583","1418–1456":"1418–1456","1420–1473":"1420–1473","25 September 1473":"25. september 1473","1473":"1473","1583":"1583","1483":"1483","1482":"1482","1436":"1436","1458":"1458","1457":"1457","1456":"1456","1455":"1455","1432":"1432","1420":"1420","1418":"1418","1504":"1504","1515":"1515","Stretton, Staffordshire, England":"Stretton, Staffordshire, England","Glazeley, Shropshire, England":"Glazeley, Shropshire, England","Stretton, Shropshire, England":"Stretton, Staffordshire, England","Stretton by Burton upon Trent, Staffordshire, England":"Stretton by Burton upon Trent, Staffordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Alderley, Cheshire, England":"Alderley, Cheshire, England","Birdstone, Herefordshire, England":"Herefordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},